1. There are two groups being compared in the study.
2. The study is measuring the decrease in corneal NV area.
3. The measurement is taken one month after injection.
4. The mean decrease in corneal NV area in group 1 is 28.4%.
5. The standard deviation of the decrease in corneal NV area in group 1 is 9.01%.
6. The mean decrease in corneal NV area in group 2 is 4.51%.
7. The standard deviation of the decrease in corneal NV area in group 2 is 11.64%.
8. The decrease in corneal NV area in group 1 is significantly higher than in group 2.
9. The p-value of the comparison between group 1 and group 2 is 0.001.

messages.content:
Statement: The mean decrease in corneal NV area one month after injection in group 1 (28.4 ± 9.01%) was significantly higher than in group 2 (4.51 ± 11.64%, p = 0.001).
